Things to be be considered
1- Create a none class with the rest position
2- Train a binary rest/active classifier to detect when the hand is in a neutral position. Use this to trigger segmentation rather than purely time-based sliding windows. Real sign language has brief pauses between words, and detecting these pauses is more reliable than fixed-stride sliding windows for inter-sign boundaries.
3- NLP layer that takes the output of the inference and checks for contextual smoothing and grammatical alignement
4- Discrizting flex sensors
5- Binariazed system for pads
6- Method of choosing gold standard (fastest, slowest, Kmeans)
7- plotting the flex and pad channels to observe them
8- Vectorized data base